      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my ac unit outside is making a loud humming noise but the fan isnt actually spinning. any idea what's wrong and is it safe to go look at it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A loud humming noise from your AC unit without the fan spinning could be a sign of a few things, such as a faulty capacitor, a problem with the compressor, or even something as simple as a loose belt. It's always best to consult a professional before attempting to inspect or fix it yourself, especially since AC units can be dangerous if not handled properly. However, if you're feeling confident and have some basic tools, you could potentially check for loose connections or a tripped circuit breaker. Remember to always follow safety guidelines when dealing with electrical appliances. If the issue isn't resolved, it's best to call in a professional. \n\nFor now, it might be wise to wait for a professional to look at it, as tampering with AC units can be risky. Here are a few steps you can take before you decide to call in a professional:\n\n1. Turn off the power to your AC unit at the circuit breaker.\n2. Check if the circuit breaker has tripped and reset it if necessary.\n3. Inspect the AC unit for any visible damage or loose components. Look for a loose belt or disconnected wires.\n\nIf you're unsure or uncomfortable with these steps, it's best to call a professional. Remember, safety first!",
